Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total. (You'll add more to the sheet after 10 minutes.)

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 4).

While beef cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board; tent with foil to keep warm.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven; carefully toss, keeping on one side.

Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Return to middle rack until veggies are tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more.

Once beef is browned all over, transfer to a second baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until beef is cooked through, ~{8-12%minutes}. Transfer to a cutting board.

> If using chicken or pork, skip this step!

== Honey Thyme Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for beef over medium heat. Add garlic and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash or two of water.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice beef crosswise.

Divide beef, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle beef with sauce and serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.